

logmsg                  System Maintenance                 logmsg




Hold COHERENT Login Message

/etc/logmsg

The file /etc/logmsg  holds the message that COHERENT displays to
prompt  the user  to log  in.  The  superuser bin  can use  ed or
MicroEMACS to change the message to whatever she prefers.

***** See Also *****

system maintenance

***** Notes *****

The  default  message consists  of  the  bell character  <ctrl-G>
followed by  the text Coherent  login:.  If the  bell annoys you,
simply delete the <ctrl-G> from /etc/logmsg.







































